{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Why\nThis is the convergence mechanism itself: reuse plan-review's novelty machinery to stop code review\nre-nagging carryover findings and to drop novel low-impact findings on UNCHANGED code, while ALWAYS\nraising novel findings on newly-changed code (the per-citation region gate is the deliberate\ndivergence from plan-review's whole-artifact floor).\n\n## What\n- **Consume the reader.** Call `latest_code_review_result(key)` (revenued-thickset-dassie) for the\n  current review's typed key to obtain prior SURFACED findings + the prior `deps` map. Key selection:\n  `session:<id>` for local reviews (set on the verdict by paradoxal-balsamic-bubblefish),\n  `change:<id>` for Gerrit.\n- **REUSE unchanged kernel primitives (no fork):** the novelty SCORING contract\n  (`review_kernel.verify.novelty_model` / `NOVELTY_SUBANSWERS`) and\n  `review_kernel.decide.rising_floor_drop(priority, novelty, *, t_novel, floor)`.\n- **NEW code-review novelty PROMPT + reviewer id.** Add `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/code_review_novelty.md`\n  (`outputs: code_review_novelty`, `execution_mode: single_turn`, `category: code-review-pass`) and a\n  `code-novelty` reviewer id used in the sub-call's `RunRequest(reviewers=[\"code-novelty\"])`. Wiring\n  mirrors plan-review's `_score_floor_novelty` runner: the diff is the domain context and the prior\n  SURFACED findings are appended to the instructions as a context block (NOT a `{{plan}}`/template\n  var). Register the reused contract at `code_review/contracts.py::register_contracts()`\n  (`contracts.register_contract(\"code_review_novelty\", novelty_model)`, importing `novelty_model`\n  from `review_kernel.verify`) — mirroring `plan_review/passes.py`; without it a\n  `RunRequest(output_schema=\"code_review_novelty\")` fails at runtime.\n  - **cites_prior_location REDEFINED for code (critical).** `NOVELTY_SUBANSWERS` shares the field\n    name `cites_prior_location`, whose kernel/plan meaning is \"same PLAN location/section/AC line\".\n    The code prompt MUST firmly redefine it so the model does not anchor on the plan meaning:\n    `cites_prior_location — does this finding point at the SAME source file AND approximately the\n    same line region (within ~10 lines) as the prior finding? (not merely the same file — the same\n    localized area)`. (This closes the epic-review advisory T1.)\n- **NEW `region_gate.py`** (`src/rebar/llm/code_review/region_gate.py`) defining the region-state\n  vocabulary + detector:\n  - Constants: `REGION_UNCHANGED = \"unchanged\"`, `REGION_CHANGED = \"changed\"`, `REGION_UNKNOWN = \"unknown\"`.\n  - **Citation basis:** a finding's cited region is derived from its `location` field (a `path` or\n    `path:line`). The detector takes the finding's cited FILE path, hashes the current file\n    (`attest._hash_file`), and compares to `prior_deps[path]`: equal → `UNCHANGED`; differ → `CHANGED`;\n    path absent from `prior_deps`, OR the finding is multi-location / absence-evidence (no concrete\n    file) / moved / renamed / any error → `UNKNOWN`. File-level in v1 (line-level deferred).\n- **NEW `region_gated_floor`** (in `code_review/workflow_ops.py`, applied over the decided advisory\n  set in the produce path before the sidecar emit — the code-review analogue of plan-review's\n  `_maybe_apply_rising_floor`, which sits after the verdict and before emit):\n  - A finding is DROPPED iff `rising_floor_drop(priority, novelty, t_novel, floor)` is true AND its\n    region is `REGION_UNCHANGED`. `REGION_CHANGED` and `REGION_UNKNOWN` NEVER drop (both raise).\n  - **Thresholds/activation (decided):** reuse the EXISTING config — `verify.novelty_drop_threshold`\n    (t_novel), `verify.novelty_priority_floor` (floor), AND `verify.novelty_drop_active` as the\n    activation/evidence gate. This introduces NO NEW config key (the epic's \"no eval-gated\n    activation flag\" = no NEW flag): the code-review floor reuses plan-review's SAME three keys, so\n    it is OFF by default and an operator opts in with evidence exactly as plan-review requires\n    (preserving the opt-in-with-evidence discipline the reviewer flagged). On top of the flag, the\n    floor also SELF-GATES: inert whenever there is no prior memory for the current key (first review,\n    or a reader error → empty prior set). Both gates must be open to drop anything.\n  - Dropped findings carry `drop_reason = \"novelty-region\"`.\n  - **Carryover labeling:** a finding that matches a prior surfaced finding (low novelty) but is NOT\n    dropped is stamped `carried_from` = the matched prior finding's id (a string; the first match if\n    several). Data model: by the time the floor runs (post-decide, in the produce path), findings\n    are plain dicts in the verdict's `advisory`/`blocking` lists — `carried_from` is added as a KEY\n    on that dict (no Pydantic model change needed; the coach already ran in-workflow, so the floor\n    strips coaching notes whose `finding_refs` point at a `carried_from`-stamped finding from the\n    verdict's `coaching` list). The finding remains surfaced.\n  - **FAIL-SAFE (full mirror of plan-review):** the whole floor is wrapped in try/except; any\n    reader/hash/compare/novelty error returns the FULL unfiltered finding set (no drops). A finding\n    with no novelty entry defaults to novelty 0.0 (carryover = kept).\n- **Neutrality (ADR 0008 Invariant 1):** the Pass-1 finder NEVER receives prior findings; only the\n  post-find novelty seam does.\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/llm/code_review/workflow_ops.py` (region_gated_floor + novelty sub-call wiring),\n  `src/rebar/llm/code_review/region_gate.py` (NEW: vocab + detector),\n  `src/rebar/llm/code_review/contracts.py` (register `code_review_novelty`),\n  `src/rebar/llm/reviewers/code_review_novelty.md` (NEW prompt),\n  `src/rebar/llm/workflow/gate_dispatch.py` (invoke the floor before emit).\n- Depends on the reader/payload (revenued-thickset-dassie) and, for end-to-end LOCAL integration, on\n  local persistence (paradoxal-balsamic-bubblefish). This story is reviewed/implemented AFTER c639\n  (+3bff) are committed on the stack, so the reader (`latest_code_review_result`) + `deps` map exist\n  in the tree; region_gated_floor UNIT tests run against a mocked reader.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] A `code-novelty` reviewer prompt (`code_review_novelty.md`) + reviewer id exist, binding the\n      reused novelty contract, with diff context + prior findings in the instructions block and\n      `cites_prior_location` redefined for source-file/line regions.\n- [ ] The `code_review_novelty` contract is registered in `contracts.register_contracts()`;\n      `rising_floor_drop` is reused UNCHANGED.\n- [ ] `region_gate.py` defines `REGION_UNCHANGED`/`REGION_CHANGED`/`REGION_UNKNOWN` used by the\n      detector, which compares a cited file's current sha256 to the prior `deps` map.\n- [ ] `region_gated_floor` drops a finding ONLY when novel AND low-priority AND `REGION_UNCHANGED`;\n      `REGION_CHANGED` and `REGION_UNKNOWN` both raise; dropped findings carry\n      `drop_reason = \"novelty-region\"`.\n- [ ] Thresholds/activation reuse the EXISTING `verify.novelty_drop_threshold`,\n      `verify.novelty_priority_floor`, and `verify.novelty_drop_active` (no NEW config key); the\n      floor is OFF by default and additionally self-gates inert with no prior memory.\n- [ ] Carryover findings are stamped `carried_from` = the matched prior finding's id (string, added\n      as a dict key), have their coaching notes stripped from the verdict, but remain surfaced.\n- [ ] Any reader/hash/compare/novelty error returns the full unfiltered finding set (no drops).\n- [ ] The Pass-1 finder receives no prior findings; only the novelty seam does.\n- [ ] Tests (mocked reader): unchanged-region low-priority novel → dropped; changed-region novel →\n      raised; absence/multi-location → UNKNOWN → raised; carryover → `carried_from` + not re-coached;\n      forced reader error → no drops."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783649625651717001,"uuid":"1f34e06a-cd4a-4da7-9797-c6816721ea97"}